    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the grid stability thing, but i've also heard plenty of people saying that the cost and the time it takes to build new plants makes it a bad bet compared to just dumping everything into battery tech and solar. if someone argues that we should just skip nuclear entirely to avoid the waste and safety issues, are they just being unrealistic, or is there a legitimate path there?",
